<Layout title="SMS Terms & Conditions | TaskRocket" description="TaskRocket SMS terms and conditions.">
  <section class="legal"><div class="container"><article><h1>SMS Terms & Conditions</h1><p>Last updated: May 2026</p><h2>Program Description</h2><p>TaskRocket sends SMS messages to users who opt in through the website form. Messages may relate to workflow review requests, demo requests, scheduling, service questions, service updates, and account communication.</p><h2>Opt-In</h2><p>Users opt in by checking the SMS consent checkbox on the TaskRocket website form. The checkbox is optional and unchecked by default. Consent is not a condition of purchase.</p><h2>Message Frequency</h2><p>Message frequency varies depending on the user's inquiry, requested services, scheduling activity, and account communication.</p><h2>Message and Data Rates</h2><p>Message and data rates may apply.</p><h2>STOP Instructions</h2><p>You can cancel SMS messages at any time by replying STOP. After you reply STOP, TaskRocket may send one final confirmation message.</p><h2>HELP Instructions</h2><p>For help, reply HELP or contact TaskRocket through the contact information on the website.</p><h2>Privacy</h2><p>SMS consent and phone numbers are not sold or shared with third parties for marketing purposes. See the <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p><h2>Supported Carriers</h2><p>Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.</p><h2>Contact</h2><p>TaskRocket<br/>Website: taskrocket.org<br/>Email: info@taskrocket.org<br/>Phone: 252-205-4287<br/>Mailing address: 217 S. Goldsboro St. Wilson NC 27893</p></article></div></section>
</Layout>
